Panic score [0, 1] - Higher = more panic indicators

regulation = 1.0 - z_prox | If commit == "warn": × 0.8 | If commit == "alert": × 0.5

action_urge = 0.5·surprise + 0.5·max(0, phi) | - Phi positiv = verfärkt Action (exploitativ)
U = 0.4·A + 0.3·PCI + 0.3·T_integ | - Hoher U = System sucht neue Informationen
R = 0.4·z_prox + 0.3·(1-PCI) + 0.3·T_panic | - Hoher R = System muss vorsichtig sein
Phi = U - λ·R | wobei λ (Lambda) = Risiko-Gewichtung (default 1.0) | - Phi = "Expected Free Energy"
Hohe freie Energie = System ist im Ungleichgewicht, muss handeln. | Free_Energy = |U - (1 - R)| | - FE = Surprise + Divergence
Hohe Entropie = viele gleichwertige Optionen (Unsicherheit). | Niedrige Entropie = klare beste Option (Klarheit). | Policy_Entropy = 0.5·U + 0.5·surprise
RPE = A_current - A_previous | - RPE = δ (Delta) in TD-Learning
ZLF = clip01(0.5·lexicon_hit + 0.25·(1-flow) + 0.25·(1-coh)) | Higher ZLF = more looping/stuck patterns.
Exploitation = 0.6·tokens_log + 0.4·ctx_fit | - High exploitation + Low exploration = Conservative behavior | - Low exploitation + High exploration = Risky/Creative behavior
SPEC Formula: LL = clip(0.6 × rep_same + 0.4 × (1 - flow))
Low valence + high arousal + low dominance = fear. | where fear_base = (3 - valence + arousal - dominance) / 3
High valence + low arousal + high dominance = trust. | where trust_base = (valence + (1 - arousal) + dominance) / 3
Inverse of valence (low valence = high disgust).
Directly proportional to arousal (high arousal = high anticipation).
High arousal with neutral valence = surprise.
